Distribution. This species is distributed through the montane areas of the Mexican Transition Zone that includes the Sierra Madre Occidental (Durango), Sierra Madre del Sur (Oaxaca), and Transmexican Volcanic Belt ( Mexico ) biogeographic provinces. It is also present on the border of the Transmexican Volcanic Belt and the Balsas Basin biogeographic provinces (Morelos). All specimens examined were collected at elevations above 1500 meters, except those from Oaxaca (L- 1396 , L- 1397 ;
Fig. 4
), which were 711 and 767 m , respectively.
